1. No smoking indoors.
2. Copy of ID or Passport upon arrival.
3. Please take shoes off when entering.
4. Please recycle (recycling bins provided).
5. Pls use white plastic bags for garbage only.
6. Pls use clear plastic ones for recycling only.
7. You are welcome to use anything provided.
8. No loud music after 9 pm.
9. Non-registered guests must leave by 9 pm.
10. Please treat The Apt as if it were your own and leave it as you've found it.

12. We will try to accommodate any possible requests so please ask!

description:
Welcome to LIC Apt!

Very cozy apartment located in a quiet, peaceful neighborhood. 
Please view the page for more details.

Thanks!

Welcome to LIC Apt.!

Northern bedroom:
 - (1) Queen size bed. Sleeps two.
 - (1) Sofa bed. Sleeps two.

Southern bedroom
 - (1) Queen size bed. Sleeps two.

Eastern bedroom/Living Room
- (1) Queen size sofabed. Sleeps two.
- (3) Twin size air mattresses. Sleeps three.

Included:
 - High speed WiFi
 - Washing machine and dryer
 - Air conditioning/Heat
 - Flat screen TV
 - Cable TV
 - Fresh, fluffy towels 
 - Fresh, crisp linen
 - Pots, pans, plates, glasses, kitchenware
 - Microwave
 - Coffee Maker
 - Toaster
 - Ironing Board/Iron

Walk/Bicycle
One block from the Queensboro Plaza (next to the Queensboro Bridge aka the 59th St. Bridge) it takes you to midtown Manhattan.
 - 20 min. 2nd Ave. and 59 St.
 - 9 min. on a bicycle to Central Park.
 - Bicycle rental two blocks away.
 - Dedicated bicycle path on the bridge.
 - You can be in the middle of NYC in literally 5 minutes.

Subway:
Three block radius to six different train stations:
 Two blocks from the N, Q and 7 trains.
  - 1 stop from the city.
  - 4 stops from Grand Central
  - 7 stops from Times Square.
 Three blocks from the E, M and R trains.
  - 2 stops from the city.
 Six blocks from the F train.
  - 2 stops from the city.

$5 - $9 Cab ride to Manhattan.

Airports:
Taxis:
 - About $19 to La Guardia
 - About $35 to JFK Airport.

LIC Apt. has the best of both worlds. Quiet and very close to the city. 

There are great restaurants and bars within walking distance. New ones open up all the time as well. 
A ten minute walk brings you to PS1, a satellite museum of MoMA. It has great, funky pieces of art from cutting edge artists. They also host summertime DJ parties. 
Hipster Williamsburg in Brooklyn is 10 min. by car.

Free and safe street parking opens up by late afternoon. 
There are also parking lots within two blocks. They charge around $9 for the day.

Please feel free to shoot me a message.

Thanks!
Adam

Relaxed and quiet area right next to Manhattan.
